The paper focuses on optimizing the reliability of software systems in Cloud environments, which is a key concern in software engineering (cs.SE). It also mentions the use of large clusters of commodity hardware, which is a characteristic of distributed computing (cs.DC). The proposed approach relies on machine learning and graph theory, which are both relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper mentions the lightweight nature of the proposed approach, which suggests a focus on efficiency and optimization, a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG).
